(7938, 'carbidopa, levodopa and entacapone', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drugs that are highly protein bound (such as warfarin, salicylic acid, phenylbutazone, and diazepam): Levodopa Levodopa is bound to plasma protein only to a minor extent (about 10% to 30%). In vitro studies have shown no binding displacement between entacapone and other highly bound drugs, such as warfarin, salicylic acid, phenylbutazone, and diazepam.', 'DailyMed'),
