(32490, 'folic acid, ferrous fumarate, ascorbic acid, cholecalciferol, .alpha.-tocopherol acetate, thiamine mononitrate, riboflavin, pyridoxine hydrochloride, cyanocobalamin, zinc oxide, cupric sulfate anhydrous, and selenomethionine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drugs which may interact with vitamin B12: Antibiotics, cholestyramine, colchicines, colestipol, metformin, para-aminosalicylic acid, and potassium chloride may decrease the absorption of vitamin B12.', 'DailyMed'),
(32490, 'carbidopa, levodopa and entacapone', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drugs that are highly protein bound (such as warfarin, salicylic acid, phenylbutazone, and diazepam): Levodopa Levodopa is bound to plasma protein only to a minor extent (about 10% to 30%). In vitro studies have shown no binding displacement between entacapone and other highly bound drugs, such as warfarin, salicylic acid, phenylbutazone, and diazepam.', 'DailyMed'),
