(29393, 'spironolactone', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Acetylsalicylic Acid (ASA): ASA may reduce the efficacy of spironolactone (7.6). 7.6 Acetylsalicylic Acid Acetylsalicylic acid may reduce the efficacy of spironolactone. Therefore, when spironolactone and acetylsalicylic acid are used concomitantly, spironolactone may need to be titrated to higher maintenance dose and the patient should be observed closely to determine if the desired effect is obtained [see Clinical Pharmacology (12.3)].', 'DailyMed'),
