(10176, 'methaver', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Drug s which may interact with vitamin B12:• Antibiotic, cholestyramine, colchicines, colestipol, metformin, para-amino salicylic acid, and potassium chloride may decrease the absorption of vitamin B12.• Nitro us oxide can produce a functional vitamin B12 deficiency.', 'DailyMed'),
